  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the grill to medium-high heat.",
    "Roll out the puff pastry on a lightly floured surface to a thickness of 1/8 inch.",
    "In a large bowl, combine the duck-confit-leg, onion, red bell pepper, tomato, and scallions.",
    "In a small bowl, whisk together the aji amarillo pepper paste, garlic, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, and black pepper.",
    "Pour the sauce over the duck mixture and toss to combine.",
    "Place the pastry on the grill and cook for 2-3 minutes or until golden brown.",
    "Transfer the pastry to a baking sheet and top with the duck mixture.",
    "Return the pastry to the grill and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes or until the filling is heated through.",
    "Serve immediately and garnish with additional scallions if desired.",
    "Cut into wedges or squares and serve hot."
  ],
